{"parse":{"title":"Ministry of Education, Universities and Research (Italy)","pageid":17748231,"revid":859857165,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-Refimprove\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"39\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/75px-Question_book-new.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/100px-Question_book-new.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"399\" /></a></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>needs additional citations for <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability\" title=\"Wikipedia:Verifiability\">verification</a></b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\" title=\"Help:Introduction to referencing with Wiki Markup/1\">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may be challenged and removed.</span>  <small><i>(November 2011)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption>Ministry of Education, Universities and Research</caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Ministero dell'Istruzione, dell'Universit\u00e0 e della Ricerca</b><br />MIUR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Emblem_of_Italy.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Emblem of Italy.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Emblem_of_Italy.svg/100px-Emblem_of_Italy.svg.png\" width=\"100\" height=\"113\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Emblem_of_Italy.svg/150px-Emblem_of_Italy.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Emblem_of_Italy.svg/200px-Emblem_of_Italy.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"390\" data-file-height=\"440\" /></a></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color: #efefef\">Agency overview</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Formed</th><td>\n2001<span style=\"display:none\">&#160;(<span class=\"bday dtstart published updated\">2001</span>)</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Jurisdiction</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_Italy\" title=\"Government of Italy\">Government of Italy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Headquarters</th><td>\nViale Trastevere, 76/a <br /> 00153 <a href=\"/wiki/Rome\" title=\"Rome\">Rome</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Website</th><td>\n<span class=\"url\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.miur.gov.it\">www<wbr />.miur<wbr />.gov<wbr />.it</a></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>Ministry of Education, Universities and Research</b> (in <a href=\"/wiki/Italian_language\" title=\"Italian language\">Italian</a>: <span lang=\"it\" style=\"font-style:normal;\"><b>Ministero dell'Istruzione, dell'Universit\u00e0 e della Ricerca</b></span> or <b>MIUR</b>) is the ministry of the <a href=\"/wiki/Council_of_Ministers_(Italy)\" title=\"Council of Ministers (Italy)\">Italian government</a> for the national education system, the Italian universities and research agencies.  The current <a href=\"/wiki/Italian_Minister_of_Education\" title=\"Italian Minister of Education\">Italian Minister of Education</a> is <a href=\"/wiki/Marco_Bussetti\" title=\"Marco Bussetti\">Marco Bussetti</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Structure\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Structure</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#National_level\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">National level</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Local_level\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Local level</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Ministers\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ministers</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Since_2001\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Since 2001</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 1988, the Ministero dell'Universit\u00e0 e della Ricerca was split off from the <a href=\"/wiki/Ministry_of_Public_Education_(Italy)\" title=\"Ministry of Public Education (Italy)\">Ministry of Public Education</a>.  In the first <a href=\"/wiki/Romano_Prodi\" title=\"Romano Prodi\">Romano Prodi</a> cabinet the two were merged back into the Ministero della Pubblica Istruzione, Universit\u00e0, Ricerca Scientifica e Tecnologica, then as the Ministero dell'istruzione, dell'universit\u00e0 e della ricerca (MIUR) in the second and third <a href=\"/wiki/Silvio_Berlusconi\" title=\"Silvio Berlusconi\">Silvio Berlusconi</a> cabinets.  The two were re-separated in the second Prodi cabinet of 17 May 2006, but then re-merged in the fourth Berlusconi cabinet of 7 May 2008.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Structure\">Structure</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Structure\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"National_level\">National level</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: National level\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>Department for ministerial planning and for ministerial management of the education budget, human resources and information</li>\n<li>Department for education</li>\n<li>Department for the universities, higher education establishments in art, music and dance,</li></ul>\n<p>The three Departments carry out policies dictated by the Ministry and form the body which directs and programs educational policy.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Local_level\">Local level</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Local level\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Regional education \"uffici\", which are autonomous administrative centres, carrying out the instructions of the Departments, directly supporting individual schools, and articulating the policies on the ground.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ministers\">Ministers</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Ministers\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Since_2001\">Since 2001</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ministry_of_Education,_Universities_and_Research_(Italy)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Since 2001\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\">Name<br /><small>(Born-Died)</small>\n</th>\n<th>Portrait\n</th>\n<th colspan=\"2\">Term of Office\n</th>\n<th>Party\n</th>\n<th>Cabinet\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\">Minister of Instruction, University and Research (MIUR)<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#0087DC;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Letizia_Moratti\" title=\"Letizia Moratti\">Letizia Moratti</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1949\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Letizia_Moratti.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Letizia Moratti.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Letizia_Moratti.jpg/70px-Letizia_Moratti.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"92\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Letizia_Moratti.jpg/105px-Letizia_Moratti.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Letizia_Moratti.jpg/140px-Letizia_Moratti.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2602\" data-file-height=\"3436\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>11 June 2001\n</td>\n<td>17 May 2006\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Forza_Italia\" title=\"Forza Italia\">Forza Italia</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#BEE1F5\"><a href=\"/wiki/Berlusconi_II_Cabinet\" title=\"Berlusconi II Cabinet\">Berlusconi II</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Berlusconi_III_Cabinet\" title=\"Berlusconi III Cabinet\">Berlusconi III</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\">Minister of Public Instruction\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#3CB371;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Giuseppe_Fioroni\" title=\"Giuseppe Fioroni\">Giuseppe Fioroni</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1958\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Giuseppe Fioroni daticamera.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg/70px-Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"97\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg/105px-Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e5/Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg/140px-Giuseppe_Fioroni_daticamera.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"165\" data-file-height=\"228\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>17 May 2006\n</td>\n<td>8 May 2008\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/The_Daisy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The Daisy\">The Daisy</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Democratic_Party_(Italy)\" title=\"Democratic Party (Italy)\">Democratic Party</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#FFDAE1\"><a href=\"/wiki/Prodi_II_Cabinet\" title=\"Prodi II Cabinet\">Prodi II</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\">Minister of Universities and Research\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#CE2029;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Fabio_Mussi\" title=\"Fabio Mussi\">Fabio Mussi</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1948\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Fabio Mussi Trento 2007.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg/70px-Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"85\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg/105px-Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg/140px-Fabio_Mussi_Trento_2007.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1853\" data-file-height=\"2244\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>17 May 2006\n</td>\n<td>8 May 2008\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Democrats_of_the_Left\" title=\"Democrats of the Left\">Democrats of the Left</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Democratic_Left_(Italy)\" title=\"Democratic Left (Italy)\">Democratic Left</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#FFDAE1\"><a href=\"/wiki/Prodi_II_Cabinet\" title=\"Prodi II Cabinet\">Prodi II</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"7\" align=\"center\">Minister of Instruction, University and Research (MIUR)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#0087DC;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Mariastella_Gelmini\" title=\"Mariastella Gelmini\">Mariastella Gelmini</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1973\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Mariastella Gelmini daticamera 2018.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg/70px-Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"97\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg/105px-Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/46/Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg/140px-Mariastella_Gelmini_daticamera_2018.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"165\" data-file-height=\"228\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>8 May 2008\n</td>\n<td>16 November 2011\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/The_People_of_Freedom\" title=\"The People of Freedom\">The People of Freedom</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#BEE1F5\"><a href=\"/wiki/Berlusconi_IV_Cabinet\" title=\"Berlusconi IV Cabinet\">Berlusconi IV</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#DDDDDD;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Francesco_Profumo\" title=\"Francesco Profumo\">Francesco Profumo</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1953\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Francesco_Profumo.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Francesco Profumo.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Francesco_Profumo.jpg/70px-Francesco_Profumo.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"94\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Francesco_Profumo.jpg/105px-Francesco_Profumo.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Francesco_Profumo.jpg/140px-Francesco_Profumo.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"263\" data-file-height=\"352\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>16 November 2011\n</td>\n<td>28 April 2013\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Independent_(politician)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Independent (politician)\">Indipendent</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"><a href=\"/wiki/Monti_Cabinet\" title=\"Monti Cabinet\">Monti</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#EF1C27;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Maria_Chiara_Carrozza\" title=\"Maria Chiara Carrozza\">Maria Chiara Carrozza</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1965\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Maria Chiara Carrozza daticamera.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg/70px-Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"97\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg/105px-Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg/140px-Maria_Chiara_Carrozza_daticamera.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"165\" data-file-height=\"228\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>28 April 2013\n</td>\n<td>22 February 2014\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Democratic_Party_(Italy)\" title=\"Democratic Party (Italy)\">Democratic Party</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#EEEEEE\"><a href=\"/wiki/Letta_Cabinet\" title=\"Letta Cabinet\">Letta</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#1560BD;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Stefania_Giannini\" title=\"Stefania Giannini\">Stefania Giannini</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1960\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Stefania_Giannini.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stefania Giannini.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Stefania_Giannini.jpg/70px-Stefania_Giannini.jpg\" width=\"70\" height=\"98\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Stefania_Giannini.jpg/105px-Stefania_Giannini.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Stefania_Giannini.jpg/140px-Stefania_Giannini.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"229\" data-file-height=\"321\" /></a>\n</td>\n<td>22 February 2014\n</td>\n<td>12 December 2016\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Civic_Choice\" title=\"Civic Choice\">Civic Choice</a><br /><a href=\"/wiki/Democratic_Party_(Italy)\" title=\"Democratic Party (Italy)\">Democratic Party</a>\n</td>\n<td bgcolor=\"#FFDAE1\"><a href=\"/wiki/Renzi_Cabinet\" title=\"Renzi Cabinet\">Renzi</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"background:#EF1C27;\">\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Valeria_Fedeli\" title=\"Valeria Fedeli\">Valeria Fedeli</a><br /><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(1949\u2013 )</span>\n</td>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/File:ValeriaFedeli.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"ValeriaFedeli.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/c